<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-01-21T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-01-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="386" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d386">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">693.0023/1–2147: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Dairen</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Benninghoff</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                            the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Dairen</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-01-21">January 21 [<hi rend="italic">18</hi>], 1947</date>.<lb/>[Received January 21—9:02
                            p.m.]</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>12. Clear text in numerals of translation of memorandum from Soviet Consul
                        following telegram.<note n="11" xml:id="d386fn1">See telegram No. 13,
                            January 18, <hi rend="italic">infra.</hi>
                        </note> Reference my telegram 10, Jan. 16 [<hi rend="italic">17</hi>]. Words
                        in paragraph 3 of “commercial ship” mean unarmed naval vessel is only
                        personal opinion Soviet Consul.</p>
                    <pb facs="0495" n="485" xml:id="pg_485"/>
                    <p>He suggests this point be cleared in Moscow, and apparently wording came from
                        Moscow.</p>
                    <p>Will take no action pending instructions.</p>
                    <p>Repeat Shanghai, Nanking, Moscow.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Benninghoff</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>